-- Rolling Stones to Make Final World Tour Next Year, Sun Says
-- Alistair Holloway
-- 2010-07-24T11:01:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-24/rolling-stones-to-make-final-world-tour-next-year-sun-says.html

          
          
             The Rolling Stones will begin a
final “full-scale” world tour next year, likely performing in
stadia,  the Sun  reported today, citing an unnamed person.  
 The band, formed in 1962, is in talks with promoters Live
Nation about the tour, the newspaper said. The tour is set to
last into 2012, it said.  
